	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=31448&mid=109788606022018>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=31448&mid=109788606022018>RE: Is this suposed to be Uber?</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=31448&mid=109788606022018#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Oct 15th 8:21 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=180152><span id= >TheSilverwinds</span></a><br><span id=notbold>29 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.76]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1>magic based most often means big resist... means no agro<hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE> Wrong. A resisted spell results in just as much aggro as a spell landing for full damage. Potential damage genereates aggro, not actual damage done.<br><br><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1>i seen em proc almost as often as they land the hit, all that matters is how fast they are swingin, and amount of dex in order to get the chance to proc. <hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE><br><br>Close but not quite. Proc rate is determined SOLELY by dex and AA (Weapon Affinity) and by Procrate mod field on the weapon. You literally do not have to swing in order to proc... as long as autoattack is on, you have the chance to proc. A 75 delay weapon unhasted will proc exactly as often (statistically) as a 17 delay weapon with 130% haste, given that both weapons have the same base proc rate, and that the character wielding them has the same amount of dex with each weapon equipped.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
